definition.value: A GDP-hexose having 6-deoxy-alpha-D-altrose as the hexose component.
A N-arachidonoylphosphatidylethanolamine where the acyl chains at the sn-1 and sn-2 positions of the glycerol molecule are unspecified.
A carboxylic acid anion resulting from the deprotonation of the carboxy group of 3-acetamido-4-hydroxybenzoic acid. The major microspecies at pH 7.3.
Major microspecies at pH 7.3
An agonist at the transient receptor potential vanilloid 1 (TRPV1).
The sodium salt of bromfenac. Note that 'bromfenac sodium' commonly refers to the sesquihydrate (120638-55-3); this is the anhydrous form.
A dialkyl phosphate having ethyl as the alkyl group; major microspecies at pH 7.3
An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by global deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of (1->4)-3,6-bis(phospho)-alpha-D-glucan; major species at pH 7.3.
Any glycerophospholipid consisting of any 1-alkyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which one of the amino hydrogens has been replaced by an acyl group.

A member of the cadinene family of sesquiterpenes in which the double bonds are located at the 4-4a and 7-8 positions, and in which the isopropyl group at position 1 is cis to the hydrogen at the adjacent bridgehead carbon (position 8a).

A carbohydrate acid derivative anion arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic acid and sulfate groups of the repeating units of heparan sulfate alpha-D-glucosaminide N-sulfate; major species at pH 7.3.
An L-alpha-amino acid residue derived from alpha-D-glucosyl-L-tyrosine.
An L-alpha-amino acid residue derived from (1,4-alpha-D-glucosyl)(n)-L-tyrosine.
An L-alpha-amino acid residue derived from alpha-D-xylose-(1->3)-beta-D-glucose-L-serine.
An L-alpha-amino acid residue derived from beta-D-glucose-L-serine.
An L-alpha-amino acid residue derived from beta-D-glucose-L-threonine.
An L-alpha-amino acid residue derived from alpha-D-xylose-(1->3)-beta-D-glucose-L-threonine.

A member of the class of isoindoles that is isoindole in which the amino group has been acylated by a 2,4-dihydroxy-5-isopropylbenzoyl group and in which position 5 of the isoidole moiety has been substituted by a (4-methylpiperazin-1-yl)methyl group. A second-generation Hsp90 inhibitor.
A glycerophospholipid obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of any carboxylic acid with the amino group of any 1-[(1Z)-alkenyl]-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine.
A substituted ethane carrying two hydroxy groups.
A 1-(alk-1-enyl)-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate in which the alk-1-enyl and acyl groups are specified as (1Z)-octadecenyl and oleoyl respectively.
Any cyanohydrin that is derived from an aliphatic aldehyde and has S-configuration.
Any cyanohydrin that is derived from an aliphatic ketone and has S-configuration.
An L-alpha-amino acid residue derived from alpha-D-xylose-(1->3)-alpha-D-xylose-(1->3)-beta-D-glucose-L-serine.
A member of the class of xanthones that is 9H-xanthen-9-one substituted by methoxy groups at positions 3 and 5 and hydroxy groups at positions 1 and 6.
An L-alpha-amino acid residue derived from alpha-D-xylose-(1->3)-alpha-D-xylose-(1->3)-beta-D-glucose-L-threonine.
Any saturated fatty acid containing 4 carbons.
Any plant metabolite that is produced by Arabidopsis thaliana.
A monohydroxybenzoic acid that is 4-hydroxybenzoic acid in which the hydrogen at position 3 has been replaced by an acetamido group.

A carbohydrate acid derivative anion arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic acid and sulfate groups of the repeating units of heparan sulfate alpha-D-glucosaminide 6-sulfate; major species at pH 7.3.
pteridine coenzyme found in S. solfataricus
An L-alpha-amino acid residue derived from S-(ADP-D-ribosyl)-L-cysteine.
A member of the class of carotenone that is echinenone carrying an additional hydroxy substituent at position 4'.
Catechol substituted at position 3 with an (8Z,11Z)-pentadeca-8,11-dien-1-yl group. Stereoisomer of urushiol III (CHEBI:9909) which has (8E,11E) configuration.
A homocystine zwitterion in which both stereocentres have L configuration.
